            "name": "Radhika Sagariya"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-06-10",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I thank the principal for reopening the Champs after pandamic. I feel proud that my daughter first step of education have been started from Champs. I thank the teachers and principal on the commitment and patience on every individual child.  With your guidance my daughter got confidence and socialism. Everyday was a learning for her. As family we thank you for the love support.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Champs Academy - Palavakkam"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "JD"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-04-08",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I have known Champs Academy Global Pre School from its conception stages and witnessed its dedicated founders Mrs.Pearl Raj & Mr.Aden Raj striving hard for over a decade to build Champs Academy into an multiple award winning institution for its high standards in quality of education.\n\nHappy Students-Happy Parents-Happy Staffs.. is what I have always seen here. Such positive environment for kids is very important for their overall growth and their future and Champs does brings out such Happy Vibes.\n\nAbove all, Champs practices one of its kind  inclusive teaching that impressed me a lot. It is such a welcoming approach in creating awareness and a healthy society..Hats off to that.\n\nExperienced and caring staff members, safe and secured environment, quality and global educational standards…Thats Champs Academy for you 👍🏻",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Champs Academy - Palavakkam"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Champa Vinodini"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-03-17",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Champs Academy- I m completely satisfied with Champs Academy. My Daughter learnt Many things in this year. Im surprised by seeing their planning, taking care of the children . The academic plan set by the team was excellent. She learnt very well. Phonics, the letter identification, counting , they teach the in depth concepts of everything  . There was a positive feeling when they welcome each child in the morning .  How come all the teachers remember every child name studying in champs ? super excited for the next year\nOnly one suggestion mam : photos and the videos can be even more clear and cover all the children whenever any event conducted in the campus . Just a suggestion. Priya mam was so kind and knowledgeable teacher. Pearl mam u r amazing. Ruby mam Energetic women .\nSureka mam I like they way you engaged the children during the annual day program back stage most of the children were crying , when u start singing the rhyme everyone stopped crying. Spontaneous teacher . All the teachers too were so energetic and helpful. Champs - Safety , planning , knowledge, kind .",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
